<section>
  <title>Dashboard Datasource</title>
  <para>Dashboards consist of a series of Panes featuring graphical
  information related to the context where they are used. You can add as many
  (or as few) Dashboard Panes as you need. The type, source data, and width of
  the Panes are user-definable.</para>
  <para>To create new a Dashboard Pane, select the ADD button. The following
  screen will appear:</para>
  <para><screenshot>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/xTDashDatasource.png" />
        </imageobject>
        <caption>Dashboard Datasource</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot></para>
  <para>When creating a new Dashboard Pane, you are presented with the
  following options:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Title</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Enter a title to identify the Pane.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Description</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Enter a brief description to describe the Pane.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
